---
import DocsLayout from '../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<DocsLayout title="JWT & Token Rotation" activeNav="jwt-auth" description="Access + Refresh token pairs with JTI-based revocation, replay detection, and scope embedding.">

  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Araxys implements a full <strong>OAuth2-compliant JWT system</strong> with access and refresh token pairs. It includes JTI (JWT ID) based revocation, automatic token rotation, and replay attack detection.
  </p>

  <h2 id="token-flow">Token Flow</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Login</strong>: User authenticates → server issues an access + refresh token pair.</li>
    <li><strong>Access</strong>: Client sends the access token in the <code>Authorization: Bearer</code> header.</li>
    <li><strong>Expiration</strong>: Access token expires (default: 30 minutes).</li>
    <li><strong>Rotation</strong>: Client sends the refresh token → server issues NEW pair, blacklists the old refresh token.</li>
    <li><strong>Replay Detection</strong>: If someone tries to reuse the old refresh token, Araxys detects it as a replay attack.</li>
  </ol>

  <div class="alert">
    <div class="alert-title">
      <span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size: 16px;">security</span>
      Replay Attack Protection
    </div>
    <div class="alert-content">
      Each refresh token has a unique JTI (JWT ID). When rotated, the old JTI is added to a blacklist. Attempting to reuse a blacklisted refresh token triggers a <code>TOKEN_REVOKED</code> audit event — a clear sign of token theft.
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>

  <h3 id="issuing-tokens">Issuing Token Pairs</h3>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code><span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys <span class="token-keyword">import</span> Scope

<span class="token-decorator">@app.post</span>(<span class="token-string">"/auth/login"</span>)
<span class="token-keyword">async def</span> <span class="token-function">login</span>(<span class="token-param">username</span>: <span class="token-builtin">str</span>, <span class="token-param">password</span>: <span class="token-builtin">str</span>):
    <span class="token-comment"># ... validate credentials ...</span>
    pair = <span class="token-keyword">await</span> shield.jwt_manager.<span class="token-function">create_token_pair</span>(
        <span class="token-param">subject</span>=user.id,
        <span class="token-param">scopes</span>=[Scope.READ, Scope.WRITE],
    )
    <span class="token-keyword">return</span> pair.<span class="token-function">model_dump</span>()</code></pre>
  </div>

  <h3 id="rotating-tokens">Rotating Tokens</h3>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code><span class="token-decorator">@app.post</span>(<span class="token-string">"/auth/refresh"</span>)
<span class="token-keyword">async def</span> <span class="token-function">refresh</span>(<span class="token-param">refresh_token</span>: <span class="token-builtin">str</span>):
    <span class="token-comment"># Old refresh token is automatically blacklisted</span>
    new_pair = <span class="token-keyword">await</span> shield.jwt_manager.<span class="token-function">rotate_tokens</span>(refresh_token)
    <span class="token-keyword">return</span> new_pair.<span class="token-function">model_dump</span>()</code></pre>
  </div>

  <h3 id="protecting-endpoints">Protecting Endpoints</h3>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code set:html={`<span class="token-keyword">from</span> fastapi <span class="token-keyword">import</span> Depends
<span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys <span class="token-keyword">import</span> Scope
<span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys.jwt_auth.dependencies <span class="token-keyword">import</span> require_jwt
<span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys.jwt_auth.tokens <span class="token-keyword">import</span> TokenPayload

<span class="token-decorator">@app.get</span>(<span class="token-string">"/profile"</span>)
<span class="token-keyword">async def</span> <span class="token-function">profile</span>(
    <span class="token-param">user</span>: TokenPayload = <span class="token-function">Depends</span>(
        <span class="token-function">require_jwt</span>(Scope.READ, <span class="token-param">jwt_manager</span>=shield.jwt_manager)
    ),
):
    <span class="token-keyword">return</span> {"user_id": user.sub, "scopes": user.scopes}`} /></pre>
  </div>

  <h2 id="configuration">Configuration</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Field</th>
        <th>Type</th>
        <th>Default</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>algorithm</code></td><td><code>Literal["HS256", "RS256", "ES256"]</code></td><td><code>"HS256"</code></td><td>JWT signing algorithm (expanded)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>access_token_ttl_minutes</code></td><td><code>int</code></td><td><code>30</code></td><td>Access token time-to-live (≥1)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>refresh_token_ttl_days</code></td><td><code>int</code></td><td><code>7</code></td><td>Refresh token time-to-live (≥1)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>issuer</code></td><td><code>str | None</code></td><td><code>None</code></td><td>JWT <code>iss</code> claim</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>audience</code></td><td><code>str | None</code></td><td><code>None</code></td><td>JWT <code>aud</code> claim</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>private_key</code></td><td><code>str | None</code></td><td><code>None</code></td><td>RSA/EC private key (PEM) for RS256/ES256</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>public_key</code></td><td><code>str | None</code></td><td><code>None</code></td><td>RSA/EC public key (PEM) for RS256/ES256</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>jwks_enabled</code></td><td><code>bool</code></td><td><code>False</code></td><td>Enable JWKS endpoint</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2 id="scopes">Permission Scopes</h2>
  <p>Araxys provides three built-in scopes via the <code>Scope</code> enum:</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Scope</th>
        <th>Value</th>
        <th>Use Case</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>Scope.READ</code></td><td><code>"read"</code></td><td>Read-only access to resources</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>Scope.WRITE</code></td><td><code>"write"</code></td><td>Create and modify resources</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>Scope.ADMIN</code></td><td><code>"admin"</code></td><td>Administrative operations</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p>Scopes are embedded in the JWT payload and validated by the <code>require_jwt</code> dependency. If a token doesn't have the required scope, Araxys returns <code>403 Forbidden</code>.</p>

  <h2 id="token-storage">Token Storage</h2>
  <p>
    JTI blacklisting requires persistent storage. Araxys auto-detects the backend:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>No Redis URL</strong> → <code>InMemoryTokenStorage</code> (development)</li>
    <li><strong>Redis URL set</strong> → <code>RedisTokenStorage</code> (production)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    When using Redis, JTI operations use <strong>atomic <code>SET NX</code></strong> to prevent race conditions — if two workers attempt to blacklist the same JTI concurrently, only one succeeds, and the other detects the conflict.
  </p>

  <div class="alert alert--warning">
    <div class="alert-title">
      <span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size: 16px;">warning</span>
      Production Note
    </div>
    <div class="alert-content">
      In-memory token storage means blacklisted JTIs are lost on server restart. Use Redis in production to persist token revocation across deployments.
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="asymmetric-algorithms">Asymmetric Algorithms</h2>
  <p>
    Araxys supports <strong>RS256</strong> (RSA PKCS#1 v1.5 with SHA-256) and <strong>ES256</strong> (ECDSA P-256 with SHA-256) asymmetric signing algorithms in addition to the default <strong>HS256</strong> (HMAC with SHA-256). When using RS256 or ES256, you must provide a <code>private_key</code> and <code>public_key</code> in PEM format.
  </p>
  <p>
    HS256 (symmetric) uses only the <code>secret_key</code> for both signing and verification. RS256/ES256 use a private key for signing and a public key for verification — the public key can be safely distributed to clients or third-party services. When using asymmetric algorithms without providing the required keys, Araxys raises a <strong><code>ConfigurationError</code></strong> at startup rather than failing silently at runtime (v0.10).
  </p>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code><span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys.core.config <span class="token-keyword">import</span> JWTConfig

<span class="token-comment"># RS256 requires PEM-encoded RSA key pair</span>
config = <span class="token-function">JWTConfig</span>(
    <span class="token-param">algorithm</span>=<span class="token-string">"RS256"</span>,
    <span class="token-param">private_key</span>=<span class="token-string">"""-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----
MIIEvQIBADANBgkqhkiG9w0BAQEF...
-----END PRIVATE KEY-----"""</span>,
    <span class="token-param">public_key</span>=<span class="token-string">"""-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----
MIIBIjANBgkqhkiG9w0BAQEFAAOC...
-----END PUBLIC KEY-----"""</span>,
    <span class="token-param">access_token_ttl_minutes</span>=<span class="token-number">15</span>,
)</code></pre>
  </div>

  <h2 id="jwks-endpoint">JWKS Endpoint</h2>
  <p>
    When <code>jwks_enabled=True</code>, Araxys registers a <code>/.well-known/jwks.json</code> route that returns the public key set in <strong>RFC 7517</strong> (JWKS) format. This allows third-party services to verify tokens issued by your Araxys shield without needing the public key configured directly.
  </p>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code><span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys.core.config <span class="token-keyword">import</span> JWTConfig

config = <span class="token-function">JWTConfig</span>(
    <span class="token-param">algorithm</span>=<span class="token-string">"RS256"</span>,
    <span class="token-param">private_key</span>=private_key_pem,
    <span class="token-param">public_key</span>=public_key_pem,
    <span class="token-param">jwks_enabled</span>=<span class="token-bool">True</span>,
)</code></pre>
  </div>

  <p>The JWKS endpoint returns a response like:</p>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">json</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code set:html={`{
  "keys": [
    {
      "kty": "RSA",
      "use": "sig",
      "alg": "RS256",
      "kid": "araxys-key-1",
      "n": "0vx7agoebGcQSu...",
      "e": "AQAB"
    }
  ]
}`} /></pre>
  </div>

  <h2 id="token-introspection">Token Introspection</h2>
  <p>
    Araxys implements a <strong>RFC 7662</strong> compliant Token Introspection endpoint. Send a <code>POST</code> request with the token to the introspection endpoint, and Araxys returns a JSON response with the <code>active</code> status and token metadata.
  </p>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code>POST /auth/introspect
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

token=eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIs...</code></pre>
  </div>

  <p>Response (active token):</p>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">json</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code set:html={`{
  "active": true,
  "sub": "user_123",
  "scope": "read write",
  "token_type": "Bearer",
  "exp": 1715000000,
  "iat": 1714998200,
  "client_id": null
}`} /></pre>
  </div>

  <p>Response (expired or invalid token):</p>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">json</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code set:html={`{
  "active": false
}`} /></pre>
  </div>

</DocsLayout>
